pageContext.description: St. bev. with 3 arc-furrows below; at least one, poss. 2 or 3, furrows on lower blade above edge bevel; four cables on fg. sides - very oblique and "S" shaped; twist along body; small punched groove in one blade tip side.
pageContext.surface: Dark olive green patina; much of one face and parts of remainder flaked to dry dull green surface; edge intact and sharp - but gold traces; bright gold along fg. crests; tips very prob. broken off in ant.
pageContext.other: Lenght: 103.3mm,Width: e. 54mm; Wbt: 16.2mm; Bfg 15mm; T st 11.5mm
pageContext.collection: Oaxham Museum, O.S. 368,Previously in collection of V.B. Crowther-Beynon
